        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 30 at 9:21AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 920 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Colorado Bend State Park, or 10 miles west of Lampasas, moving east
at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Lampasas around 930 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Nix and Rumley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
